<doc id="339468" wikidata="Q28923870" url="?curid=339468" title="Acritoscincus">
<text>Acritoscincus is a genus of Australian skinks (family Scincidae). It belongs to the &quot;Eugongylus&quot; group; the genus &quot;Oligosoma&quot; appears to be a fairly close relative. An alternative name is Bassiana.

==Species==
*&quot;Acritoscincus duperreyi&quot; (Gray, 1838) -- eastern three-lined skink, bold-striped cool-skink
*&quot;Acritoscincus platynotus&quot; (Peters, 1881) -- red-throated cool-skink, red-throated skink
*&quot;Acritoscincus trilineatus&quot; (Gray, 1838) -- southwestern cool-skink, western three-lined skink, New Holland skink
==References==</text><links>
